  "id": "kimi-code-cli-native-agent-derived",
  "title": "Kimi Code CLI-native coding agent architecture (v0.2.0 refresh, May 2026) (Hidden Structure)",
  "source": "Derived via Hidden Structure from kimi-code-cli-native-agent. Source observation: Extracted 2026-05-26 from MoonshotAI/kimi-code tag @moonshot-ai/kimi-code@0.2.0 commit d496fd40b649ddec1226b8f44cf1556c51178aff source tree, package manifests, and docs/en. Exact v0.2.0 tag/branch name was absent from the remote branch probe; GitHub DNS then blocked ls-remote, so the tagged local MoonshotAI/kimi-code checkout was cloned into research/repos/kimi-code. System: kimi-code. Version: 0.2.0. Edge convention: X depends on Y = X talks to, loads, invokes, configures, gates, or receives runtime results/events from Y. The schema v0.3 used by this repository forbids an extra top-level system field, so system identity is recorded here.",
  "narrative": {
    "mode": "walkthrough",
    "steps": [
      {
        "caption": "<strong>Step 1.</strong> Hidden Structure has sorted the system. Every node sits on the diagonal in a position that reveals its structural role.",
        "reveal": {
          "include": [
            "diagonal"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "caption": "<strong>Step 2.</strong> Forward transfers show the dependency flow as it actually runs. Below the diagonal, each mark is a direct invocation or load.",
        "reveal": {
          "include": [
            "diagonal",
            "transfer:directed:forward"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "caption": "<strong>Step 3.</strong> Backward transfers — above the diagonal — show where the system loops back on itself. These are the cycles that make ordinary topological sorting impossible.",
        "reveal": {
          "include": [
            "diagonal",
            "transfer:directed:forward",
            "transfer:directed:backward"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "caption": "<strong>Step 4.</strong> The four-square partition.<br/>Core: 18 nodes in a mutually-dependent cycle.<br/>Shared: 6 nodes the core depends on.<br/>Control: 2 nodes that depend on the core.<br/><em>Architecture: core-periphery.</em>",
        "reveal": {
          "include": [
            "diagonal",
            "transfer:directed:forward",
            "transfer:directed:backward",
            "overlay:module-border"
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
  },
